commit.message:
add field for the name of a moduleInstantiation

Co-authored-by: Erik Krogh Kristensen <erik-krogh@github.com>
Allow module applications to the right of `::`

Refactor `signatureExpr`

Also adds a uniform interface to all of the `::`-qualified entities.

(Combining all of these into their own AST node is left as future work.)
Push `implements` field inside as well.

Push `parameter` field into list

This ensures that get the right return type for `getParameter` in QL.
Add field for module qualifier
Add field for signature expression arity
Add fields for `moduleParam`
Rename `Application` to `Instantiation`
Finish parameterised module support and tests

Fix aggregate test

I think this one was broken since the rollback of how `unique` was
parsed.
Whitespace fixes
Support unary parameterised modules
Allow empty class declarations

Autoformat

Somehow, this file had a lot of instances where a space was replaced
with another space-like character. I blame my keyboard.
Support trailing commas in set literals
Re-add `unique` as an `aggId`

Add support for `instanceof`

Also tries to make this fork of the grammar more in line with the
official repo.

Change precedence of unary op.

Puts it just below prefix casts, as `-(float) 5` is interpreted as
`-((float) 5)` by the original grammar.
Fix misparse for unary ops
